find

public java.lang.Object find(java.lang.Class inputClass,
                             java.lang.Object inputParams)
                      throws jtscException,
                             jtscExceptionUser,
                             jtscExceptionServer,
                             jtscExceptionChannel
Use this commande for find object. Please not create Object, use this commande for not beak persistance System. Valable Object : 
UserObject : Find with id(Integer) or name(String)
ServerObject : Find with portId(Integer) or name(String)
ChannelObject : Find with channelId(Integer) or name(String)
BanObject : Find with banId(Integer)
Code Exemple: find with port : server server1 = (server) jtscPersistant.find(server.class,8767); find with serverName : server server1 = (server) jtscPersistant.find(server.class,"server team");

Parameters:
inputClass - Object find : server.class user.class channel.class banObject.class
inputParams - Find expressions.
Returns:
Correct object , user, banObject, sever or channel.
Throws:
jtscException - if object is not findable.
jtscExceptionUser - if userNot found
jtscExceptionServer - if server not found.
jtscExceptionChannel - if channel not found.
